==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Depict
<hw>De*pict"</hw> <pr>(d⟦esl⟧*p⟦icr⟧kt")</pr>, <pos>p. p.</pos> <ety>[L.
<ets>depictus</ets>, p. p. of <ets>depingere</ets> to depict;
<ets>de-</ets> + <ets>pingere</ets> to paint. See <er>Paint</er>, and
cf. <er>Depaint</er>, <pos>p. p.</pos>]</ety> <def>Depicted.</def>
<rj><au>Lydgate.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><-- p. 393 --></p>

<p><ent>Depict</ent>⟦br⟧

==== ENTRY 2 ====
HEADWORD: Depict
<hw>De*pict"</hw> <pr>(d⟦esl⟧*p⟦icr⟧kt")</pr>, <pos>v. t.</pos>
<vmorph>[<pos>imp. & p. p.</pos> <conjf>Depicted</conjf>; <pos>p. pr. &
vb. n.</pos> <conjf>Depicting</conjf>.]</vmorph> <sn>1.</sn> <def>To
form a colored likeness of; to represent by a picture; to paint; to
portray.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>His arms are fairly <qex>depicted</qex> in his chamber.</q>
<rj><qau>Fuller.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>To represent in words; to describe
vividly.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>C⟦ae⟧sar's gout was then <qex>depicted</qex> in energetic
language.</q> <rj><qau>Motley.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>depicted</ent>⟦br⟧
